        <section class="about column-contain">
            <article>
                <header>
                    <h2>About Marionette</h2>
                </header>
                <p>
                    Backbone.Marionette is a composite application library for Backbone.js that aims to simplify the construction of large scale JavaScript applications.
                </p>
                <p>
                    It is a collection of common design and implementation patterns found in the applications that we have been building with Backbone, and includes pieces inspired by composite application architectures, event-driven architectures, messaging architectures, and more.
                </p>
            </article>
            <div class="quick-links">
                <nav>
                    <h3>Quick Links</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <a href="https://github.com/marionettejs/backbone.marionette", target="_blank">Marionette.js on GitHub</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="http://marionettejs.com/docs/backbone.marionette.html", target="_blank">Annotated Source Code</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
                <nav>
                    <h3>Requirements</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="http://jquery.com/", target="_blank">jQuery</a> <span>v1.8+</span></li>
                        <li><a href="http://underscorejs.org/", target="_blank">Underscore</a> <span>v1.4.4+</span></li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="http://backbonejs.org/", target="_blank">Backbone</a> <span>v1.1.x</span>
                            <p class="note">
                                is preferred. v1.0.0, v0.9.9 and v0.9.10 should work still
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/marionettejs/backbone.wreqr", target="_blank">Backbone.Wreqr</a></li>
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/marionettejs/backbone.babysitter", target="_blank">Backbone.BabySitter</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
            </div>
          <div class="cl"></div>
        </section>
